{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"75fad340-b7d0-4ecb-b57f-92888f6ac349","content":"The working directory is empty, so I'll answer from knowledge.\n\n## Migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform\n\n### 1. Update your test projects\n\nAdd the MTP runner and the extensions you need:\n\n```xml\n<!-- In each test .csproj -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Platform.MSBuild\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n```\n\n### 2. Replace VSTest@3 with `dotnet test`\n\n**Before:**\n```yaml\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testAssemblyVer2: '**/*Tests.dll'\n    resultsFolder: $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n```\n\n**After:**\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: Run tests\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >\n      --configuration Release\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      -- \n      --report-trx\n      --report-trx-filename TestResults.trx\n      --coverage\n      --coverage-output-format cobertura\n```\n\n### 3. Publish the results\n\n```yaml\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: Publish TRX results\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: Publish code coverage\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n### Key differences to note\n\n| Concern | VSTest@3 | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|---|\n| Runner | `vstest.console.exe` | Built into `dotnet test` |\n| TRX output | Automatic | Opt-in via `--report-trx` |\n| Coverage | `codeCoverageEnabled` | `--coverage` flag |\n| Test filter | `testFilterCriteria` | `--filter` argument |\n\nThe `--` separator passes arguments directly to the MTP runner (everything after it is not interpreted by `dotnet test`).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"764ad020-1a91-44df-9943-1e8c08eec8e0","outputTokens":605,"requestId":"9849:C5472:170100:1E42DA:69FFD84E"},"id":"31f3b37d-6207-46f0-b361-927d673eb482","timestamp":"2026-05-10T00:59:05.568Z","parentId":"dea94547-ec30-477c-a2e3-c6aa8883be12"}
